@ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress = http://localhost:5204

### View seeded products and their stock levels
GET {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/products

### 1. Place a valid order (success path)
POST {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 1,
  "quantity": 2
}

### 2. Place another order to reduce stock
POST {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 2,
  "quantity": 2
}

### 3. Try to over-order — insufficient stock (409 Conflict)
POST {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 2,
  "quantity": 99
}

### 4. Try to order an out-of-stock product (409 Conflict)
POST {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 3,
  "quantity": 1
}

### 5. Try to order a product that doesn't exist (404 Not Found)
POST {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 999,
  "quantity": 1
}

### 6. Try to order with invalid quantity (422 Unprocessable)
POST {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": 1,
  "quantity": 0
}

### 7. Get a specific order
GET {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders/1

### 8. Get an order that doesn't exist (404 Not Found)
GET {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders/999

### 9. Cancel the first order (success — stock is restored)
POST {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders/1/cancel

### 10. Try to cancel again (409 Conflict — already cancelled)
POST {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders/1/cancel

### 11. View all orders
GET {{ResultPatternDemo_HostAddress}}/orders
